SIMPLE: palea
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Palea
<hw>Pa"le*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Pale⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(-⟦emac⟧)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.,
chaff.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The interior chaff or
husk of grasses.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the chaffy scales or
bractlets growing on the receptacle of many compound flowers, as the
Coreopsis, the sunflower, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A pendulous process of the skin
on the throat of a bird, as in the turkey; a dewlap.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Paleaceous</ent>⟦br⟧
